          "width": "16"
        }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
            "fillRule": "evenodd",
            "d": "M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"
          }}></path></svg></a>{`Executing the Arbitrage Orders`}</h2>
    <p>{`If the calculated arbitrage size is greater than 0, the arbitrage strategy would simultaneously send both the market buy and market sell orders to the two markets. However, arbitrage opportunities are usually rare and quickly exploited by traders, so it is important to send both orders out without any wait.`}</p>
    <p>{`The order execution logic can be found in the function `}<code parentName="p" {...{
        "className": "language-text"
      }}>{`c_process_market_pair_inner()`}</code>{` inside `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/CoinAlpha/hummingbot/blob/master/hummingbot/strategy/arbitrage/arbitrage.pyx"
      }}>{`arbitrage.pyx`}</a>{`.`}</p>

